    <!-- Grading Breakdown -->
    <h3 style="color:#002147; margin:16px 0 8px;">Grading Breakdown</h3>
    <div style="border:1px solid #d6dbe5; padding:10px 12px; background:#ffffff; margin-bottom:12px;">
      Student performance will be assessed through a combination of exams, assignments, and applied activities. Four unit exams (60 pts lecture + 40 pts lab) will assess comprehension of material through in-person testing. SmartBook assignments (120 pts) and case histories (40 pts) provide opportunities to practice and apply concepts in an adaptive, low-stakes format. The comprehensive final exam (100 pts) will include both lecture and lab content. The remaining portion of the grade comes from lab quizzes (100 pts).
    </div>

